article.description: — Jawaun Daniels had 30 points as Prairie View rolled past Alabama A&M 72-48 on Monday night.
article.headline: Daniels scores 30, leads Prairie View past Alabama A&M 72-48
article.linkText: Daniels scores 30, leads Prairie View past Alabama A&M 72-48
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- — Jawaun Daniels had 30 points as Prairie View rolled past Alabama A&M 72-48 on Monday night. Daniels hit 11 of 12 shots, including 6 of 6 from behind the arc. He added seven rebounds. D'Rell Roberts had 11 points for Prairie View (4-12, 4-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Markedric Bell added four blocks. Christian Guess had six rebounds. Prairie View dominated the first half and led 44-16 at halftime. Jalen Johnson had 15 points for the Bulldogs (4-13, 3-4). Abba Lawal added 11 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
